        "title": "fix: use Object.hasOwn instead of in operator in usage bar translator",
        "body": "Related: #98466\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes `key in table` matching inherited `Object.prototype` properties.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nReplace with `Object.hasOwn(table, key)` in alias lookup and case table (2 locations).\n\n## User Impact\n\nFixes incorrect usage bar rendering when keys coincide with prototype names.\n\n## Evidence\n\nRuntime verification (fix/in-operator-prototype, rebased on upstream/main 6495358f):\n\n```\ntranslator.test.ts — Test Files 1 passed, Tests 15 passed\n✓ alias — prototype keys do not match inherited properties\n✓ map — prototype keys do not match inherited properties, fallback to _default\n✓ alias — listed shortens, unlisted echoes through\n... (15/15 ✓, Duration 320ms)\n```\n\nIncludes 2 regression tests: `toString`/`constructor` in alias and map paths.",
